import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=10, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['age'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['age'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    avg_age = data['age'].mean()
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    ax.bar(['Average Age', 'Average Height'], [avg_age, avg_height], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e'])
    ax.axhline(avg_age, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Age: {avg_age:.2f}')
    ax.axhline(avg_height, color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Height: {avg_height:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average age and height of the people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    plt.bar(name_counts.index, name_counts.values, color='blue')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What are the most common names in the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
